sd=Special Pricing Conditions	Maintain a pricing list or conditions (with ranges and optional terms) categorized by various dimensions to impose exceptional product pricing conditions that override standard pricing terms (for special events/situations)	The bank suspends certain product fees during a major brand awareness campaign	This service domain allows the bank to apply special pricing terms and conditions that override standard price calculations. These override facilities are to be used in specific situations where a bank level decision is taken to amend prices or pricing terms in response to some major event or business development action
